                            <comment id="12847198" author="bmargulies" created="Fri, 19 Mar 2010 01:46:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Progress: there is a distribution dir. The maven/pom.xml is gone.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Yet to do:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;fix up the eclipse setup department. Use dependencySet instead of fileSet in the distribution descriptors. Reconsider the question of the merged source archives.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12894285" author="srowen" created="Sat, 31 Jul 2010 16:06:12 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Benson is this as fixed as it&apos;s going to be for now or you want to do more?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894371" author="bmargulies" created="Sun, 1 Aug 2010 12:41:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s one leftover to deal with. the Directory &apos;maven&apos; remains, containing an &apos;ant&apos; build file and some other misc, that overlaps the etc dir. I think it should be moved into etc, and not all the packaging is as I promised. I&apos;ll make some time this week.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906492" author="bmargulies" created="Mon, 6 Sep 2010 13:05:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I moved the build.xml into etc. I removed the duplicate site.xml. I move the residual eclipse setup files that no one is using in any case to sit next to the files that are in use in case anyone has a use for them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12906498" author="hudson" created="Mon, 6 Sep 2010 13:38:36 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #250 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/250/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/250/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-338&quot; title=&quot;Simplify maven structure&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-338&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-338&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;: move build.xml used from some poms to &apos;etc&apos; to clean out the vestigal &apos;maven&apos; directory&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
